-- WI-744: the ONLY fault is an import that names no module — the top-level fact
-- below is valid and DID answer before the fix. `collect_queries` printed
-- `warning: unresolved import ...` and ran the query anyway, exit 0, so the
-- pattern's short names were left to resolve by accidental scope walk (or not at
-- all) and the user got a confident wrong answer in place of a diagnostic.
--
-- Twin of good-query.anthill; keep the two in the same shape.
namespace probe.q
  import no.such.module.Nope
end

fact probe.db.Person.mk(name: ?n, age: ?a)
